         <abstract>
            <p>This paper examines the implications of forward- and backward-looking monetary policy rules in an environment with monetary-fiscal interactions. We find that the unique stationary rational expectations equilibrium (REE) is always non-Ricardian under simple implementable monetary policy rules.</p>
          </abstract>
